commText: Philip Salt and Narine are at the crease. Philip Salt is on strike. Bhuvneshwar will open the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, 1 run, swinging away from a length outside off, Salt throws his hands on the cut and slices it off the thick outside half to the right of third man
Bhuvneshwar to Narine, wide, short of length angling down leg, Narine looks to help it fine but no dice
Bhuvneshwar to Narine, no run, fuller with a hint of curl into the left-hander, Narine was shaping up to go hard but ends up dragging the slog to the right of mid-on
Bhuvneshwar to Narine, no run, the length is too full this time around, Narine slices the drive to the right of Samad at cover

Bhuvneshwar to Narine, 1 run, Narine made room early and Bhuvi was smart enough to deny any width outside off and bowl it full into the pads, Narine mistimes the drive to the right of Cummins at mid-on for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, no run, good length outside off, Salt punches but can't beat the off-side ring
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, no run, beauty from Bhuvneshwar, bowls a I0$ inswinger in the channel and has Salt prodding, only to sniff it past the outside edge
Marco Jansen, comes into the attack
Marco Jansen to Narine, 1 run, I0$ makes room and biffs the full delivery off the cue end to the right of mid-on

Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, no run, looks to heave a back of a length delivery from outside leg and misses, the ball lobs to short fine off the thigh pad. Salt clearly lost his shape trying to power that on the leg-side
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, wide, full and angling away wide of off, Salt looks to smash it through the off-side and gets beaten on the outside edge

Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, SIX, there comes the first big hit of the night! Full and slanting away outside off, Salt lofts it with a slightly open bat face and manages to clear the sweeper cover fence with lovely timing
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, SIX, gee! Thiis one is even better. Short and sat up nicely in the outside off corridor, Salt says thank you and flays it for another maximum square on the off-side

Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, SIX, Salt wants to break his own records - for hitting the biggest six of the night. He bends his back knee slightly, waits for the juicy length delivery and thumps it over extra cover for a mighty maximum
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, out Narine Run Out!! Narine had given up too soon. To be fair, he's been batting that attitude for quite a while now and the game to send him up the order didn't quite work as expected for KKR. So, after getting belted for a hat-trick of sixes, Marco Jansen wasn't too pleased and dug it short on the stumps. Salt hops and fends it awkwardly off the splice towards backward point and was ball-watching briefly. His partner, Narine, though was anything but ball-watching. He ran halfway down the pitch and just gave up on seeing the ball dribble to backward point. Shahbaz took aim and hit the bulls-eye. Narine run out (Shahbaz Ahmed) 2(4)
Venkatesh Iyer, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Bhuvneshwar to Venkatesh Iyer, 1 run, drifting in from a length, Iyer clips to the left of short fine leg for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, no run, keeps it in the corridor of uncertainty and gets it whistling past the poking blade of Philip Salt
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, no run, terrific stuff from Bhuvneshwar. Once again tests Salt in that fifth stump channel and gets the ball dancing past the outside edge yet again
Bhuvneshwar to Philip Salt, 1 run, drops the length delivery with soft hands into the off-side and hurries across for a quick single
Bhuvneshwar to Venkatesh Iyer, no run, swings away sharply from a fullish length, Iyer was opened up on the defence and gets beaten on the outside edge
Bhuvneshwar to Venkatesh Iyer, 2 runs, full and angled in at the pads
T Natarajan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
T Natarajan to Philip Salt, 1 run, length delivery on the stumps, Salt heaves it to the left of mid-on and Markram puts in a diving stop to prevent a certain boundary

T Natarajan to Venkatesh Iyer, FOUR, comes dancing down the wicket, picks the full delivery off his pads and hoicks the flick to the right of the fielder at short fine. The pace of Natarajan takes care of the rest...
T Natarajan to Venkatesh Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Venkatesh Iyer, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! Bowler, batter and fielder - the left-handed trio if I can call that. Venkatesh Iyer had that adrenaline rush after that previous boundary and once again wanted to use his feet to claim a boundary. He was quick to run down but Natarajan did well to shorten his length by a fraction and that meant Iyer ended up chipping the flashy drive straight to the fielder at cover. Venkatesh Iyer c Marco Jansen b T Natarajan 7(5) [4s-1]
Shreyas Iyer, right handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Shreyas Iyer, no run, good length just outside off, Shreyas Iyer taps into the off-side and looks for a quick single, sent back!
T Natarajan to Shreyas Iyer, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Cummins!! The skipper goes for a duck. 50th IPL wicket for Natarajan. Once again it's the length that did the trick for him. Not too full and not too short. Managed to hit that in-between length and Shreyas Iyer's attempted drive finds the toe of the bat. Cummins, stationed at mid-off, had to leap full length to his left and he took a wondrous catch over his head with lovely composure. Shreyas Iyer c Cummins b T Natarajan 0(2)
Nitish Rana, left handed bat, comes to the crease

STAT: Phil Salt is the 13th batter to have opened the innings for KKR since 2022. No other team has used more than eight openers in this period. Salt and Narine: 15th opening pair for KKR since 2022, the next most by a team is 9 by SRH.
T Natarajan to Nitish Rana, no run, full and just outside off, Nitish Rana pushes it into the off-side
Pat Cummins, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Cummins to Philip Salt, no run, good length just outside off, Salt hops and taps it into the covers
Cummins to Philip Salt, 1 run, full outside off, Salt pushes the drive wide of cover
Cummins to Nitish Rana, no run, back of a length on off, chopped away to backward point
Cummins to Nitish Rana, FOUR, one bounce and over the ropes! Banged in short on middle and leg, Nitish Rana swivels and pulls it comfortably over square leg
Cummins to Nitish Rana, no run, cuts the I0$ length delivery and gets an inside edge to the left of Jansen at slip
Cummins to Nitish Rana, 2 runs, short and wide of off, Rana pulls off the thick inside half and manages to get it wide of Bhuvi at mid-on for a couple of runs

Summary: Overs 1-5 - 39/3 -- Tidy 1st over from Bhuvi who finds some swing  -- Salt smashes 3 successive sixes vs Jansen  -- Narine run-out for 2 & Bhuvi bowls another superb over -- Natarajan removes both the Iyers in his opening over
T Natarajan to Philip Salt, wide, bumper sprayed down leg, Philip Salt doesn't bother with it
T Natarajan to Philip Salt, 1 run, opens the bat face and punches the length delivery square on the off-side
T Natarajan to Nitish Rana, 1 run, shuffles across and picks the full delivery off his pads, an easy clip away to deep backward square leg
T Natarajan to Philip Salt, no run, full and wide of off, Salt cue-ends the drive to mid-off
T Natarajan to Philip Salt, 1 run, I0$ angled in from a length, Salt chops it off the thick inside edge to the left of short fine
T Natarajan to Nitish Rana, no run, I0$ good length angling away outside off, Nitish Rana looks for a late dab and gets beaten on the outside edge
T Natarajan to Nitish Rana, no run, good length just outside off, bunted away to the right of mid-on
Marco Jansen [1.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, no run, short and angling away outside off, Salt looks to guide it fine and was a bit late in opening the bat face. Past the bat once again...
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, 2 runs, Jansen goes full and Salt is happy to show a straight bat on the drive, past the diving effort of mid-off and long-on tidies up to keep it down to two
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, 1 run, width on offer, Salt slashes it away to the right of third man
STAT: KKR lost 29 wickets in the powerplay last season, the most among the 10 teams. For context, CSK had lost just nine in 15 innings.

Marco Jansen to Nitish Rana, 1 run, dropped. Tough chance, but by IPL standards it will count as a drop. Nitish Rana made room early to clear the off-side ring, but the length was a bit more shorter than expected. He looks to slap, and ends up chipping it off the splice to the right of cover where Samad fails to cling on. He had to run back with his outstretched right hand and only managed fingertips on it...
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, 2 runs, advances and slogs the length delivery to the right of the fielder at long-on
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, no run, dabbed away into the off-side
Mayank Markande, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Markande to Nitish Rana, 1 run, comes down the track and flicks the quicker delivery to the right of square leg
Markande to Philip Salt, 1 run, tossed full outside off, Salt goes hard on the drive and hits it to the left of sweeper cover
Markande to Nitish Rana, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Markande to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Tripathi!! Premeditated and it backfires. Nitish Rana had made up his mind to play the switch hit even before the ball was bowled and he ended up chipping a dolly of a catch to backward point. Didn't really get the desired timing and dragged it off the thick inside half straight to Tripathi inside the ring. Nitish Rana c Tripathi b Markande 9(11) [4s-1]
Ramandeep Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Markande to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, run-out check sent upstairs but Salt has made his crease. Cut away to backward point and Ramandeep Singh was off for a quick single, Salt was slightly hesitant but managed to drag his bat inside the line in the nick of time
Markande to Philip Salt, no run, quicker outside off, Salt stabs it to cover
Markande to Philip Salt, 1 run, goes on the back foot and crunches the flatter delivery along the ground to the right of sweeper cover
Pat Cummins [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Philip Salt, 1 run, full on the stumps. clipped away to fine leg

Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, FOUR, Cummins tests Ramandeep Singh with a I0$ bumper on the stumps, Ramandeep pulls and gets a glove that ricochets off the helmet and over the keeper in the blink of an eye...
Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, no run, full on middle and leg, Ramandeep flicks and finds Samad at the edge of the circle on the leg-side (mid-wicket)
Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, good length just outside off, punched away to the left of mid-on for a quick single
Cummins to Philip Salt, 1 run, short of length outside off, Salt clears his front leg and heaves the pull to the right of deep mid-wicket

Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, another short ball and Ramandeep gets into a great position to smack the pull flat over the deep square fence. Rolled the wrists nicely and got the desired result as well...
Time-out!
Markande to Philip Salt, 2 runs, dropped short outside off, Salt goes deep inside the crease and cuts it to the left of sweeper cover
Markande to Philip Salt, 1 run, short once again, cut away square on the off-side
Markande to Ramandeep Singh, 2 runs, googly on middle and leg, Ramandeep goes on the back foot and nudges it into the mid-wicket pocket
Markande to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, too short and punished! Ramandeep quick to rock back and nail this drag down over wide long-on for a 90-metre maximum
Markande to Ramandeep Singh, no run, quicker legbreak just outside off, Ramandeep looks to push into the off-side and gets beaten on the outside edge
Markande to Ramandeep Singh, no run, quicker on off stump, tapped back to the left of the bowler

Summary: Overs 6-10 - 38/1 -- A tough chance and Samad drops Rana (7) -- Rana reverses and perishes to Markande -- First boundary in 22 balls - a streaky one -- Ramandeep in attacking mode as KKR score 24 runs off 2 overs
Marco Jansen [2.0-0-26-0] is back into the attack
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, FOUR, length ball sits up nicely in the slot outside off, Salt stays leg-side of the delivery and bashes it in the gap between long-off and sweeper cover
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, 1 run, a heave-ho this time and Salt finds the fielder at long-on to his right
Marco Jansen to Ramandeep Singh, no run, looks to dab a short of length delivery and gets beaten on the outside edge

Marco Jansen to Ramandeep Singh, SIX, Marco Jansen unfurls the bumper and Ramandeep says he is up for the challenge. Swivels and targets the shortest area of the ground, the pull travels all the way for a 63-metre maximum over fine leg
Marco Jansen to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, clipped off the pads to the right of fine leg
Marco Jansen to Philip Salt, 2 runs, short and wide of off, Salt hops and stabs it to the right of sweeper cover

Shahbaz Ahmed to Ramandeep Singh, no ball, SIX, Ramandeep is having a ball. Took the helmet off before the start of this over, saw the floaty delivery just outside off and lofted it inside out over extra cover with an air of authority. It was almost as if he pictured that shot in his mind well before the ball was bowled. And to make matters worse for SRH, it is a front foot no ball from Shahbaz Ahmed...
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ramandeep Singh, no run, Ramandeep looks to slog a quicker delivery and loses shape in the process, ends up chopping it off the thick inside edge into the off-side
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, driven down to long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Philip Salt, no run, forces the full delivery to the left of cover
Shahbaz Ahmed to Philip Salt, 1 run, quicker on the stumps, eased down to long-on
Shahbaz Ahmed to Ramandeep Singh, 1 run, full on the stumps, Ramandeep pushes the drive to long-on and brings up the 50-run stand

Shahbaz Ahmed to Philip Salt, FOUR, quicker and shorter outside off, Salt transferred his weight onto the back foot and spanked it past the fielder at cover to his left. Long-off ran across to his left, but had no chance of stopping that. 14 off the over
Pat Cummins [2.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack
Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Cummins to Ramandeep Singh, out Caught by Markande!! The skipper brings himself back and provides the breakthrough straightaway. He perhaps knew that Ramandeep was expecting something short or full. Served neither though. Hit the good length real hard and got some extra zip off the surface, Ramandeep wanted to loft the drive over the off-side ring but chipped it off the inside half to the right of cover where Markande times his leap to absolute perfection before grabbing a terrific catch. Ramandeep Singh c Markande b Cummins 35(17) [4s-1 6s-4]
Rinku Singh, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Cummins to Rinku Singh, FOUR, no sighters needed says Rinku Singh. Sees the full ball outside off and smacks the drive up and over mid-wicket with absolute disdain
Cummins to Rinku Singh, 1 run, Cummins bangs it short outside off, Rinku opens the bat face and steers it fine of third man
Cummins to Philip Salt, 1 run, swivels and heaves the short ball to the right of deep mid-wicket
Cummins to Rinku Singh, no run, short of length just outside off, Rinku hops and tucks it to the left of mid-wicket
Cummins to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, length ball drifting into the pads, flicked away to the right of fine leg. Easy two...
Mayank Markande [2.0-0-15-1] is back into the attack
Markande to Philip Salt, no run, 84.6kph, leans forward to slap-drive, can't get it past the bowler

Markande to Philip Salt, FOUR, fifty for Philip Salt! 82.6kph, trifle short, there's width on offer as well, Philip Salt rocks back and hammers the cut through extra cover. First match for KKR and it's been a sensible knock from Salt. Raises his bat...
Markande to Philip Salt, 1 run, 93.2kph, quicker one, hurriedly pulled to deep square leg off the inner half of the bat
Markande to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 80.9kph, tossed up, full and wide of off, driven along the ground to long-off
Markande to Philip Salt, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Markande to Philip Salt, out Caught by Marco Jansen!! SRH's catching has been really good today. 90.1kph, in-drifter that doesn't spin, Philip Salt rocks back and gets down on one leg to pull it into the stands. Dosn't get it off the middle of the bat and pays the price. Jansen moves to his right from deep midwicket and times his dive to snaffle it with both hands. Philip Salt c Marco Jansen b Markande 54(40) [4s-3 6s-3]
Andre Russell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Markande to Russell, no run, 93.6kph, off-stump line, may have been the googly, Russell watchfully defends from the crease
Cummins to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 117.6kph, off-speed back of a length delivery from round the wicket, Rinku Singh scythes it to the right of backward point who makes a diving stop
Cummins to Russell, no run, 139.8kph, short ball that zips off the deck, Russell takes his eyes off the ball as he fends awkwardly. Hits the top part of the bat before rolling towards point

Highest score on debut innings for KKR (IPL) 158* B McCullum v RCB Bengaluru 2008 64 M Pandey v MI Abu Dhabi 2014 58*Owais Shah v Deccan Mumbai DYP 2010 54 J Kallis v CSK Chennai 2011 54 P Salt v SRH Kolkata 2024
Cummins to Russell, 1 run, 143.9kph, Cummins goes fuller and Russell moves leg-side to mow it across the line. Inside-edges to deep midwicket for a single
Cummins to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 144.3kph, hint of width and that's been steered to third man
Cummins to Russell, no run, 115.kph, slower delivery, Russell clears his front leg to heave it away over the on-side. Swings early and fails to make contact. Russell wears a smile...
Cummins to Russell, 1 run, 141.1kph, yorker length, Russell stays leg-side to slice it through cover

Summary: Overs 11-15 -- Jansen continues to be expensive - 14 runs off his 3rd over -- Another 14-run over; fifty partnership between Salt & Ramandeep -- Superb catch from Markande to end Ramandeep's blitz -- A fifty on KKR debut for Phil Salt -- Salt gets out trying to pull a half-tracker from Markande
Markande to Russell, SIX, 83.5kph, tossed up, full and in the slot, Russell gets down on one leg to nail the slogsweep. Dispatched over cow corner for a 91m six
Markande to Russell, no run, wide called and SRH review it. Russell shoulders arms against this leggie that's mighty close to the tramline. Just inside and that's a dot ball. Good review
Markande to Russell, no run, quick on middle and leg, Russell defends
Markande to Russell, SIX, 86.7kph, clobbered! Scrambled seam leggie, fullish in length, Russell is down on one leg to slogsweep over deep midwicket for a 102m maximum
Markande to Russell, SIX, third six of the over. Another one in the slot and Russell doesn't miss out. Thumped over long-on for a 96m maximum. Markande under pressure

Markande to Russell, no run, wow! Markram runs in from long-off, dives forward to take a low catch. He's claiming the catch but the umpires send it upstairs. Excellent effort from the South African but that's been deemed not out by the third umpire. Full around off and Russell couldn't quite get under it as he decided to loft it downtown. Brilliant stuff from Markram but he probably couldn't get his fingers underneath the ball. The visual wasn't too clear as well and Russell survives...
Timeout!
Bhuvneshwar Kumar [2.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack
Bhuvneshwar to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 138.4kph, on a length and around off, Rinku Singh pats it wide of backward point for a single
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, SIX, 136.4kph, in-slanting length ball, Russell clears his front leg to heave it over deep midwicket for an 82m six. Russell muscle!

Bhuvneshwar to Russell, FOUR, four more! Bhuvneshwar pulls his length back by a fraction and once again Russell rocks back and clears his left leg. Pummels it in front of square on the leg-side with a powerful pull shot. Replays show that it was a slower delivery
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, 1 run, very full and wide of off, Russell reaches out and drives to long-off
Bhuvneshwar to Rinku Singh, 2 runs, low full toss around leg, flicked to deep square leg for a couple of runs

Bhuvneshwar to Rinku Singh, FOUR, 141kph, nicely done by the left-hander. Low full toss outside off and Rinku Singh opens his bat-face to perfectly place it in the gap. Beats backward point to his left and there's no one to stop that. Another 18-run over!
T Natarajan [2.0-0-9-2] is back into the attack
T Natarajan to Russell, 1 run, 121.1kph, slow and into the wicket, Russell miscues the slap to long-off
T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, 1 run, shortish ball, dabbed to short third man
T Natarajan to Russell, wide, slower ball bouncer, Russell picks it late and tries to ramp it over the keeper. Wided for height
T Natarajan to Russell, wide, 130.8kph, Natarajan goes full but spills it down leg, past Russell's flick

T Natarajan to Russell, SIX, fifty partnership! 133.1kph, Natarajan misses his yorker and ends up bowling it in the batter's arc. Leg-lined, too full and Russell swings it over deep midwicket for an 88m six
T Natarajan to Russell, 1 run, 131.4kph, yorker, tails in a bit as well and Russell flicks it away to deep midwicket
T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, no run, second bouncer of the over, pace off again ajnd Rinku Singh ducks under it
T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, FOUR, overpitched, Rinku Singh backs away, gets under it and hits through the line. One bounce and into the long-off fence. 15 runs off the over!

Bhuvneshwar to Russell, no ball, FOUR, 137.1kph, in-angling full toss on leg and Russell flicks it away through midwicket. Off the inner edge but the ball has the legs to reach the fence. Bhuvneshwar has overstepped as well
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, 1 run, very full and wide of off, Russell reaches out and loses his shape in the process as he drills it to deep extra cover
Bhuvneshwar to Rinku Singh, 1 run, 136.9kph, in the blockhole, Rinku Singh pushes it towards cover
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, SIX, 20-ball fifty for Andre Russell! 136.6kph, bouncer, the batter swings hard for a pull and gets a fat top-edge that flies over fine leg. This is Russellmania!
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, wide, Bhuvneshwar bowls this too wide outside off, left alone
Bhuvneshwar to Russell, 2 runs, full toss, flayed away to deep extra cover
STAT: Andre Russell's first fifty vs SRH. He had three unbeaten scores of exactly 49 against them before today.

Bhuvneshwar to Russell, SIX, 138.6kph, six over covers! Full and wide of off, Russell clears his front leg as he gets down on one leg, he reaches out and carves it over sweeper cover. Right off the meat of the bat and he's admiring his shot. Incredible power hitting!

Bhuvneshwar to Russell, FOUR, 130.6kph, Bhuvneshwar persists with the line outside off, the length is on the shorter side and Russell spanks it just wide of extra cover. Brute power and the ball reaches the fence in a jiffy. 26 runs off the over and KKR get to 200
T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

T Natarajan to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Markram!! The 81-run stand has been broken. 126.9kph, short of length ball wide of off, Rinku Singh decides to smash it over midwicket despite the line. Doesn't middle it. More height than distance. Markram settles under the skier at deep midwicket to take a calm catch. Rinku Singh c Markram b T Natarajan 23(15) [4s-3]
Mitchell Starc, left handed bat, comes to the crease
T Natarajan to Starc, FOUR, 130.3kph, low full toss outside off, Starc reaches out and flays it through point to get off the mark with a boundary
T Natarajan to Starc, 1 run, yorker, jammed to long-on
Due to slow over-rate, SRH have an additional fielder inside the 30-yard circle for the final over
T Natarajan to Russell, 1 run, 133kph, almost in the blockhole, Russell moves leg-side but can't get under it, drives towards long-off
T Natarajan to Starc, 1 run, chipped to long-off who takes it on the bounce
T Natarajan to Russell, 1 run, 132kph, another one in the blockhole, a backing away Russell knocks it to long-on. KKR finish on 208/7!

21:18 Local Time, 15:48 GMT, 21:18 IST: Strong finish for the hosts! On a belter, KKR were reduced to 51/4 in the eighth over. Mind you, Phil Salt got going by smashing three successive sixes against Jansen in the just the second over. The Kolkata batters gifted their wickets away - Narine run-out, Venkatesh and Shreyas perishing while playing aerial shots and Rana falling while attempting a reverse-hit. Ramandeep Singh came out all guns blazing and provided the much-needed impetus to the innings. Salt fell after notching up his fifty which brought the two power-hitters together. Russell joined Rinku and went berserk. Smashed three sixes an over off Markande and it was just the start of something spectacular. Brute power on display and the Jamaican recorded a 20-ball fifty. 85 runs off the last five overs! SRH were really good with their fielding but they didn't execute their plans in the death overs apart from Natarajan's final over. Nevertheless, not much assistance for the bowlers here and don't rule out SRH. Reply coming up shortly...

Phil Salt: Funny how this game works, really happy to be with such an amazing franchise and hope we get our first points tonight. It was slightly sticky with the new ball, and when the ball becomes old it becomes slightly easier. Back (of a length) and top of the stumps is quite tricky, and hope our seamers can do something similar. I am just happy that I am going there and delivering for the team under pressure with such a huge crowd here.

KKR innings progression: Overs 1-8: 53/4 (RR: 6.625) - including a 20-run over Overs 9-12: 52/0 (RR: 13) Overs 13-15: 18/2 (RR: 6) Overs 16-19: 77/0 (RR: 19.25) Last over: 8/1 Andre Russell vs Bhuvneshwar Kumar in the IPL Runs: 97 Balls: 37 Dismissals: 1 SR: 262.16 4s/6s: 9/8 Dots: 10 200-plus sixes in IPL 357 - Chris Gayle (141 innings) 257 - Rohit Sharma (238 innings) 251 - AB de Villiers (170 innings) 239 - MS Dhoni (218 innings) 235 - Virat Kohli (230 innings) 228 - David Warner (177 innings) 223 - Kieron Pollard (171 innings) 203 - Suresh Raina (200 innings) 200 - Andre Russell (97 innings)

Highest partnerships for 7th wicket or below in the IPL 100 - Harbhajan Singh & Jagadeesha Suchith (MI vs PBKS), Mumbai WS, 2015 91* - AB de Villiers & Iqbal Abdulla (RCB vs GL), Bengaluru, 2016 91 - Chris Morris & Kagiso Rabada (DC vs MI), Mumbai WS, 2017 88* - Rashid Khan & Alzarri Joseph (GT vs MI), Mumbai WS, 2023 81 - Andre Russell & Rinku Singh (KKR vs SRH), Kolkata, 2024 78 - Eoin Morgan & Rahul Tripathi (KKR vs DC), Sharjah, 2020

Welcome back. KKR in a huddle and Shreays Iyer has a smile on his face. His players look pretty calm. For SRH, Abhishek Sharma comes in as the impact player for Natarajan. He'll be Mayank Agarwal's opening partner. Starc has the new ball in his hand. A slip in place and off we go...
